 MEN of the Ondo State Police Command have exhumed the body of a suspected cultist killed and buried in a shallow grave at Zion Area of Igbokoda, headquarters of Ilaje Local Government Area of the state. There was a cult clash in the area at the weekend in which one person was killed and others injured. The deceased was said to have been hurriedly buried by members of his cult gang. Three persons have however been arrested in connection with the killing. Police spokesman Tee-Leo Ikoro said the three suspects were in the custody of the State Criminal Investigation Department of the command, adding that investigation was ongoing.  